<br>
No, it won't be super easy.  But if something is harder for you, then you work harder.  If you have learning disabilities it is your parents and your schools responsibility to point them out while in k-12.  If your parents refuse to believe that you have a problem they need a serious kick in their ass. <br>
<br>
If you can make it into a University and fall under $25k (net income not gross) a year you are eligible for a full pell grant $2000 a semester and up to $5000 in subsidized loans per semester.  You also receive certain moneys to go to summer school.  All you have to do is keep a 2.0 which if you are not A or B should be able to attain.<br>
<br>
Decius, not a flame towards you but just pointing out things you said.  You said one meal a day?  What is it?  I can buy a bag of rice and make lots of meals.  Or Ramen.  Do I like them?  Not really, but you learn to live on what you can.  I am lucky that for one or two years my grandparents stepped in so I could get on my feet since neither of my parents care.  <br>
<br>
