It's absurd not to believe that there's real people that just can't make it when, well, they are there. I don't care why they didn't made it. Maybe they are stupid. Maybe they had terrible luck. Maybe they have an undiagnosed mental problem. Who cares? The fact is, while I own a small company now and live reasonably well, next year I can become stupid, have bad luck, become alcoholic, get depressed by a dead son, or need a new heart... why not? we're humans, and humans fail. <br>
<br>
I want a decent second chance, and I want others to have a decent second chance as well (not only people with wealthy families should have one). State spends money painting walls, watering grass, and doing many unimportant things: giving people more chances to prosper is a great benefit to the whole society, and the state just can't forget that. We're not talking only about the moral problem. We're talking about less crime, and better chances for the poor to gain wealth.<br>
<br>
If I lose my company, I want an adequate time to find a job where I can put my technical knowledge to work. No, I don't want to work in a McDonalds as a first option, and no, in my country that salary can't pay my family's bills. I have had much worse jobs than that when needed, but I think the benefit for myself *and* for my country will be larger if I can look for a job for a few months without the pressure of being kicked out of my home. <br>
<br>
About sales tax: it is applied here in Spain and in the rest of Europe(I think ). sometimes I hate it and I am sure it slows economy a bit, but companies are not affected that much and it can even help sometimes.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=577826">Echtelion HeavyHand</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
